 class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Managerial record by team and tenure\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Team\n!rowspan=2|From\n!rowspan=2|To\n!colspan=5|Record\n|-\n!{{abbr|P|Matches played}}!!{{abbr|W|Matches won}}!!{{abbr|D|Matches drawn}}!!{{abbr|L|Matches lost}}!!{{abbr|Win %|Win percentage}}\n|-\n|align=left|[[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]] (caretaker)\n|align=left|January 2014\n|align=left|June 2014\n{{WDL|20|3|5|12|decimals=1}}\n|-\n|align=left|[[Clyde F.C.|Clyde]]\n|align=left|June 2014\n|align=left|February 2017\n{{WDL|118|46|22|50|decimals=1}}\n|-\n|align=left|[[Kelty Hearts F.C.|Kelty Hearts]]\n|align=left|October 2018\n|align=left|\n{{WDL|51|35|9|7|decimals=1}}\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n{{WDLtot|189|84|36|69|decimals=1}}\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===As a player===\n====Club====\n;Rangers<ref name=gersBF/><ref name=\"sway\">{{cite web|title=B. Ferguson|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/barry-ferguson/828/|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=18 February 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish Premier League]] (5): [[1998-99 Scottish Premier League|1998\u201399]], [[1999-2000 Scottish Premier League|1999-00]], [[2002-03 Scottish Premier League|2002\u201303]], [[2004-05 Scottish Premier League|2004\u201305]], [[2008-09 Scottish Premier League|2008\u201309]]<ref>{{ cite news | url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/scot_prem/8062744.stm| publisher=BBC Sport| first=Andy |last=Campbell| date=24 May 2009 | title=Dundee United 0-3 Rangers}}</ref>\n*[[Scottish Cup]] (5): [[2000 Scottish Cup Final|1999-00]], [[2002 Scottish Cup Final|2001\u201302]], [[2003 Scottish Cup Final|2002\u201303]], [[2008 Scottish Cup Final|2007\u201308]], [[2009 Scottish Cup Final|2008\u201309]]\n*[[Scottish League Cup]] (5): [[1998 Scottish League Cup Final|1998\u201399]], [[2002 Scottish League Cup Final|2001\u201302]], [[2003 Scottish League Cup Final|2002\u201303]], [[2005 Scottish League Cup Final|2004\u201305]], [[2008 Scottish League Cup Final|2007\u201308]]\n\n;Birmingham City<ref name=\"sway\" />\n*[[Football League Cup]] (1): [[2011 Football League Cup Final|2010\u201311]]\n\n;Individual\n*[[PFA Scotland Young Player of the Year]] (1):[[1998\u201399 in Scottish football#Individual honours|1998\u201399]]\n*[[SFWA Footballer of the Year]] (2): [[1999\u201300 in Scottish football#Individual honours|1999-00]], [[2002\u201303 in Scottish football#Individual honours|2002\u201303]]\n*[[SPFA Players' Player of the Year]] (1): [[2002\u201303 in Scottish football#Individual honours|2002\u201303]]\n*[[Scottish Premier League monthly awards|SPL Player of the Month]] (4): [[Scottish Premier League 2000-01#Monthly awards|November 2000]], [[Scottish Premier League 2000-01#Monthly awards|December 2000]], [[Scottish Premier League 2001-02#Monthly awards|February 2002]], [[Scottish Premier League 2002-03#Monthly awards|January 2003]]\n*Ferguson became a Member of the [[Order of the British Empire]] (MBE) on 17 June 2006.<ref name=MBE2/><ref name=\"mbe\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/front_page/5087176.stm |publisher=BBC Sport |title=Thorpe/Ferguson head honours list |date=16 June 2006 |accessdate=27 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n===As a manager===\n====Club====\n;Kelty Hearts\n*[[Lowland Football League|Lowland League]] (1): [[2019\u201320 in Scottish football|2019\u201320]]<ref name=KH20/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=11073 Barry Ferguson playing stats] at [[Soccerbase]]\n*{{SFA profile}}\n* [http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football/rangers-fc/barry-ferguson-5143/scottish-league-appearances_a14442/ Rangers profile at ''Sporting-Heroes.net'']\n*[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/authors/barry-ferguson Ferguson's column at the ''Daily Record'']\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{SPFA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{SPFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{SFWA Footballer of the Year}}\n{{2006\u201307 PFA Scotland SPL Team of the Year}}\